President Obama has declared a major disaster in Kentucky and ordered federal aid to assist in recovery efforts after severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding occurred from June 19-23, 2011. The federal funding will be available to local governments, certain nonprofit organizations, and for hazard mitigation measures. Steven S. Ward has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.